# dotfiles repo for $HOME — paired with `git config status.showUntrackedFiles no`.
#
# Strategy:
#   - Untracked files at $HOME root (caches, creds, IDE state, language toolchains,
#     nested project repos, app state) are hidden by the showUntrackedFiles=no
#     config, NOT by ignore rules. Don't re-add a $HOME-root deny list here —
#     the deny list was unmaintainable (every new app dropped a new untracked
#     dir we had to chase).
#   - This file's job is now narrower: keep `git add <dir>` safe for the
#     deny-then-whitelist regions (.config/, .local/, .gemini/, .tmux/plugins/),
#     and pattern-block build artefacts inside tracked subtrees.
#   - To inspect what's untracked at $HOME: `git status -uall` (one-shot opt-in).
#   - .ssh/ and other cred dirs are not in this file. They stay untracked because
#     showUntrackedFiles=no hides them; if you ever `git add` one explicitly,
#     that's a deliberate decision and you should split secrets out first
#     (see CLAUDE.md → Phase 1 ssh Include directive plan).
#
# When adding a new tracked file:
#   - At $HOME root: just `git add <path>`. Won't show in `git status` until added.
#   - Under .config/, .local/, .gemini/: add a `!`-rule per level, same pattern
#     as before (`!/.config/foo/`, `!/.config/foo/**`). Open every directory level.

# editor / shell backups (apply repo-wide so they don't sneak into tracked subtrees)
*~
*.swp
*.swo
\#*\#
.\#*

# build artefacts inside any tracked subtree
**/target/
**/node_modules/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db

# ============================================================
# .config/: app-state-heavy, deny-then-whitelist for `git add` safety
# ============================================================
/.config/*
!/.config/alacritty/
!/.config/alacritty/**
!/.config/autostart/
# autostart: third-party apps drop their own .desktop files + mimeinfo.cache.
# Re-deny dir contents + whitelist ours.
/.config/autostart/*
!/.config/autostart/org.fcitx.Fcitx5.desktop
!/.config/environment.d/
!/.config/environment.d/im-fcitx5.conf
!/.config/fcitx5/
!/.config/fcitx5/**
# fcitx5 rewrites cached_layouts on every run; never re-add it.
!/.config/fcitx5/conf/**
/.config/fcitx5/conf/cached_layouts
# keyd: source-of-truth copy of /etc/keyd/default.conf (keyd itself reads /etc/, not here).
!/.config/keyd/
!/.config/keyd/**
!/.config/systemd/
!/.config/systemd/**

# ============================================================
# .local/: deny-then-whitelist
# ============================================================
/.local/*
!/.local/bin/
/.local/bin/*
!/.local/bin/mqpub
!/.local/bin/mqsend
!/.local/bin/mqstop
!/.local/bin/zoxide-seed.sh

# ============================================================
# .gemini/: cred-bearing app dir — strict whitelist, NEVER use **
# ============================================================
# Contains oauth_creds.json, google_accounts.json, installation_id, history/,
# mailbox/. Whitelist files one by one.
/.gemini/*
!/.gemini/settings.json
!/.gemini/bin/
/.gemini/bin/*
!/.gemini/bin/talk_claude.sh
!/.gemini/skills/
!/.gemini/skills/**

# ============================================================
# .tmux/plugins/: TPM owns most plugins; we track tmux-jump-rust submodule + INDEX
# ============================================================
/.tmux/plugins/*
!/.tmux/plugins/tmux-jump-rust
!/.tmux/plugins/INDEX.md
